window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>It's time for a new kind of economy</b> </p> <p>We're overusing the earth's finite resources, and yet excessive consumption is failing to improve our lives. In <i>Enough Is Enough</i>, Rob Dietz and Dan O'Neill lay out a visionary but realistic alternative to the perpetual pursuit of economic growth-an economy where the goal is not more but enough. </p> <p>They explore specific strategies to conserve natural resources, stabilize population, reduce inequality, fix the financial system, create jobs, and more-all with the aim of maximizing long-term well-being instead of short-term profits. Filled with fresh ideas and surprising optimism, <i>Enough Is Enough</i> is the primer for achieving genuine prosperity and a hopeful future for all.</p>"; 
